  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. The value of <span class=\"italic\">k</span> can be found using the slope-intercept form of a linear equation, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals, m x plus b\"></span>, where <span class=\"italic\">m</span> is the slope and <span class=\"italic\">b</span> is the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-coordinate of the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-intercept. The equation <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"a, x plus, k y equals 6 \"></span> can be rewritten in the form <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals, the negative of the fraction a, x, over k, end fraction, plus, the fraction 6 over k\"></span>. One of the given points, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"with coordinates 0 comma negative 3\"></span>, is the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-intercept. Thus, the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-coordinate of the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-intercept <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 3\"></span> must be equal to <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction 6 over k\"></span>. Multiplying both sides by <span class=\"italic\">k</span> gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 3 k, equals 6\"></span>. Dividing both sides by <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 3\"></span> gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"k equals negative 2\"></span>.<p>Choices B, C, and D are incorrect and may result from errors made rewriting the given equation.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
